  "blurb": "A landmark three-level estate on the Plai Laem peninsula with 270-degree panoramic sea views — its signature a pair of infinity pools angled to catch both sunrise and sunset. Four sea-view en-suites, gym, sauna, games room and koi-pond gardens, on 1,800 m² in a gated enclave.",
  "detail": "Set in a private, gated enclave on Koh Samui's northeastern peninsula, this is one of the island's most exceptional hilltop estates — roughly 1,200 m² of built area on an 1,800 m² plot, with a near-total seclusion and 270-degree panoramic sea views that capture both sunrise and sunset from an elevated position with ocean on three sides.\n\nArranged across three levels for indoor-outdoor flow, the home's defining feature is a pair of infinity-edge pools strategically oriented to the morning and evening light, set among landscaped gardens, koi ponds and cascading water features. The main level opens a grand living and dining volume to expansive terraces and open-air salas, served by a full western kitchen, with all four en-suite bedrooms enjoying sweeping sea views.\n\nWellness and entertainment run deep — a professionally equipped gym, a sauna and jacuzzi positioned for the view, a games room with pool table and a separate TV lounge — backed by serious infrastructure: solar power, a full-capacity generator, deep-well supply, staff quarters and gated parking for four. Offered fully furnished and freehold, it sits within walking distance of Tongson and Samrong bays and five minutes from Choeng Mon village.",
